President Biden has declared a major disaster in Tennessee due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred on August 7, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is available to governments and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Yolanda J. Jackson of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.